{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"b295c29b-732e-45a3-be77-a0c622733dd5","content":"Good news — with .NET 10 SDK, `dotnet test` natively uses the Microsoft.Testing.Platform protocol. The `TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport` property is **no longer needed** and can be removed. It was a bridge for .NET 9 and earlier.\n\nYour project just needs:\n\n- `EnableMSTestRunner` → keeps MTP as the test host ✅\n- `TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport` → **remove it**, .NET 10 handles this automatically\n\nWant me to remove that property from your `TestProject.csproj`?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"27c26a9c-4c0e-4f4e-bfb1-de41d5867517","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is on .NET 10 SDK (10.0.100) and is using MSTest with Microsoft.Testing.Platform (MTP) via `EnableMSTestRunner`. They have `TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport` set to `true`.\n\nIn .NET 10, `dotnet test` natively supports Microsoft.Testing.Platform without needing the `TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport` property. This property was needed in .NET 9 and earlier to bridge `dotnet test` with MTP-based test projects. In .NET 10, MTP is the default test runner protocol for `dotnet test`.\n\n\nSince .NET 10 has native MTP support, they can safely remove that property from their project file — `dotnet test` will work seamlessly with `EnableMSTestRunner` without it. I should let them know this is a cleanup opportunity and offer to help update their configuration.","outputTokens":407,"requestId":"0834:5FAF2:7E29C3D:8C630F2:69EABF31"},"id":"76b1d0c8-7b64-4764-b902-ecb0ffe8b37d","timestamp":"2026-04-24T00:54:18.877Z","parentId":"c4aac9eb-d3e5-4e37-ae19-c8ab3508c53e"}
